    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Generally speaking, it was never reliable to to me to switch branches in `status-mobile` and just stop and restart processes like metro and shadow-cljs. I would easily get zombie processes such as watchman with the error you reported in this issue, or a zombie shadow-cljs compiling nothing, or another dangling gradle process consuming lots of GBs.\r\n\r\nI do think we can fix this, but at the same time, I got a bad habit of just calling a shell alias to kill everything that could have been started related to status-mobile whenever I switch branches :shrug:",
